<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Hays Code's impact on Hollywood films included:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Promoting artistic freedom</option>
            <option letter="b">Restricting content deemed morally objectionable</option>
            <option letter="c">Encouraging controversial themes</option>
            <option letter="d">Supporting political commentary</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Hays Code significantly impacted Hollywood films by establishing strict moral guidelines that restricted content deemed objectionable. The code prohibited or limited depictions of violence, sexual content, drug use, and challenges to authority. This self-imposed censorship system, developed in the 1920s and strictly enforced from 1934, shaped Hollywood film content for several decades.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
